Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi has embarked on his first tour of Europe this year. During his trip, he has already held talks with French President Emmanuel Macron and Italian Deputy Prime Minister Antonio Tajani, and is scheduled to visit Hungary and Russia as well. According to experts, this visit will contribute greatly to promoting strategic cooperation between China and the EU and advancing multi-polarization. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Michelle Van den Bergh explains.